cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on sentence embeddings and syntax. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves unsupervised learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Tree-LSTM also suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses textual entailment and reverse dictionary tasks, which are related to natural language understanding and could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well.
